# 🤟 Sign Language Detection System

> A deep learning-based system that detects sign language gestures from video input and translates them into words — bridging communication for the hearing-impaired community.

---

## 📌 Overview

This project implements a **Sign Language Gesture Recognition** system using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN). It processes video input, identifies hand gestures frame by frame, and maps each gesture to its corresponding word — making communication more accessible for people with hearing impairments.

---

## 🎯 Motivation

Communication barriers faced by hearing-impaired individuals inspired this project. By automating sign language recognition using deep learning, this system aims to:

- Reduce dependency on human interpreters
- Enable real-time gesture-to-text translation
- Promote inclusivity through assistive technology

---

## 🧠 Model Architecture

| Component        | Details                              |
|-----------------|--------------------------------------|
| Architecture    | Convolutional Neural Network (CNN)   |
| Framework       | TensorFlow + Keras                   |
| Input           | Video frames (gesture sequences)     |
| Output          | Predicted word label per gesture     |
| Training Data   | Labeled sign language gesture dataset|

### Pipeline

```
Video Input → Frame Extraction → Preprocessing → CNN Model → Gesture Label (Word)
```

